                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p><ref target="https://www.archaeology.ie/archaeological-survey-ireland/historic-environment-viewer-application">National Monuments Service</ref> SMR ID: <idno type="HER">KK024-062009-</idno></p>
                                    <material type="stone">Stone type unknown</material> 
                                    <objectType key="monument">Pillar</objectType>                                     
                                    <dimensions unit="m" source="MAC1945">                                         
                                            <height>1.56</height>
                                            <width>0.51</width>
                                            <depth>0.26</depth>
                                        <!--<dim type="diameter">if circular, etc</dim>-->
                                     </dimensions>         
                                </support>
                                <condition>The inscription is badly damaged, particularly the vowels. Damage to the stone has removed <q>scores which might have been present</q> and <q>the arris on both sides are fractured and rugged, making an accurate reading of vowels impossible</q> (McManus 1991, 75). Additionally, the face of the stone has been spalled away both at the top and the bottom (McManus 1991, 75).</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="vertical" rend="arris-up">The inscription is on the two angles of the stone and may have read upwards on each angle and finishing along the top edge of the stone.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>The ogham letters are <rs type="execution"  key="pocked" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/11.html">pocked</rs> in broad short scores. 
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
