                        <provenance type="found" when="1983">One of two ogham stones (see also I-KIK-009) at this early church site, which also has a round tower (KK024-062004-). Believed to have been removed from Tullaherin monastic site and used as a gate post on lands of Lar Mahon at Loughboreen for 30 years until re-discovered and recorded by Fionnbarr Moore in 1983 and returned to Tullaherin.  
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">On site at Tullaherin, erected close to the round tower in 1983. Situated immediately S of the S wall of the nave of the medieval church (KK024-062001-) at the W end.</provenance>
